jumpto:
The island resort's main pier, able to accommodate large cruisers and transport ships.
There is a giant welcome sign with a cat paw symbol and an information board at the entrance.
It leads, of course, to the premium juice stand run by the infamous green cat.
1.name: Pier Area

jumpto:
A luxurious haven at the heart of the resort. Also known as the resort's residential area.
Even your bones will exhale a sigh of bliss when you sink into that feather duvet.
2.name: Residential Area

jumpto:
The villa's core indoor amusement area. It has surged in popularity ever since its reopening.
Many skipped breakfast the next morning, causing concern for Chang Feng and some others.
It might be time to consider measures to prevent people from getting hooked on this place.
3.name: Indoor Area

jumpto:
At the center of the semicircular cloister sits a gazebo, where several pebble paths converge.
Inside, a simple writing brush and paper lie on the table, with a few short poems already written.
This seems like the perfect place to create poems and discuss refined subjects.
4.name: Outdoor Area

jumpto:
Docks for yachts by the beachside. Heaven on earth for those who love fishing.
People who couldn't catch anything always end up at the nearby fish market before heading home.
That market is, of course, run by the green cat.
5.name: Beach Area

jumpto:
This old lighthouse has regained its function of guiding maritime traffic.
Some rooms aren't suitable for use anymore – a fact whose mystique draws in many an adventurer.
6.name: Lighthouse Area

jumpto:
The spacious and well-lit living room of the villa. A cushy couch stands in front of the floor-to-ceiling windows, beyond which a picturesque ocean stretches on.
There is an exhibit featuring some items repurposed by the Recyclers, who've been trending lately. These items produce a unique atmosphere.

The villa's dining room features a varied and luxurious menu that caters to the tastes of all its guests.
However, the area linking it to the kitchen now has tight security for an upcoming cooking contest.
Who could warrant such caution?

This large open-air pool has received rave reviews these days, despite becoming a bit lonesome at night.
While only the attentive and inquisitive would know, this place is always on the Commander's nightly stroll route.。

The sacred oasis for the port's tabletop gamers. Its game library is so extensive, you could call it a mini-museum for board games.
Various old-school games are displayed under glass cases, each one with a fascinating story to tell.

A place for billiards aficionados. Newcomers are welcome as well.
Naturally, some guests with ulterior motives come here in pursuit of novel encounters.

The villa's art gallery showcases everything from classical oil paintings to modern sculptures,featuring many renowned pieces.
It exudes sophistication and pure elegance.

A massive game room beneath the villa. More than big enough to host events for over 100 people.
Staying here for too long will make your sense of time rather hazy.
Surely, no one would think of this as the perfect place to work overtime.

The entrance to the Palm Hall. Open to everyone.
According to management's rules, takeout food can only be delivered to the front entrance. We appreciate your understanding and cooperation.
Please do not attempt to enter by breaking through walls, rappeling down the skylight, or any other illegal means.

This area is hugely popular among outdoor enthusiasts. Just pitch your tent and you're all set for camping.
The one thing to be careful of is the dubious mushrooms hidden in the bushes.
Surely nobody would eat those and get food poisoning... right?

These elegant steel gates guard the entrance to the extravagant villa.
Past them, your laid-back and relaxing vacation begins... or does it?
Following the storm, repairing the gates has become one of the top priorities.

A quiet, beautiful, serene place... is what it was before it suffered extensive damage in the storm.
Fortunately, Evertsen and Zeven's delicate care has brought life back to the garden.
It was all thanks to "magic" – allegedly.

A tower by the side of the villa's garden. Reaching the top of the spiral staircase gives you a stunning, sweeping view of the islands.
The basement is usually used for storing gardening tools and raw materials.
However, the groundskeeper rarely locks the door.

A small, round pavilion situated in the artificial lake. Reachable by boat.
When you're fed up with the beach, enjoying the lakeside view here is a great alternative.

No true resort is complete without a Sardegnian public bath!
(This statement is merely a statement held by some Sardegnian shipgirls.)
The water, smelling of cream, cleanses your skin while washing away the fatigue in your body and spirit.

The tennis court in the outdoor amusement area is beloved by the port's sports enthusiasts.
It's where the girls sweat in the sun and sometimes gaze at the end of the road with expectation in their eyes.
They can't afford to burn all their energy before the most important spectator shows up.

The core of the beach area, offering shopping, changing rooms, and a place to relax.
There is also a private changing room just for the Commander. No entry for unauthorized personnel.

This open-air plaza was created from an empty plot of land on the beach. Perfect for festivities.
There is a music festival happening here 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.
Remember to take your litter with you after you've enjoyed the music!

A refreshing sea, smooth sands, and rows upon rows of beach parasols...
This is the ultimate vacation spot, where every grain of sand holds the secret to relaxation.
Have all the fun you want, but do not race water scooters or use drones as surfboards. It's plain dangerous.

The starting point of the golden beach that stretches on for 100 meters.
Here, you can kick back and get an unobstructed view of the beautiful coastline.
There's no better place to relish the island's gorgeous sights.

A supplies storage in the deepest part of the lighthouse. The walls are extremely sturdy.
If you were to get trapped down there... you might want to look around. Maybe a miracle will happen.

A mountain all but concealed by a thick forest. You can easily get lost here if you're not careful, but it's the only way to the lighthouse.
It's recommended you bring a companion if you're visiting this place.
